Package com.amplifyframework.core.model.annotations

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    AuthRule
    AuthRule is used define an authorization rule for who can access and operate against a Model or a ModelField.
    BelongsTo
    This annotation is used to indicate that a field is foreign key to another class that extends Model.
    HasMany
    This annotation is used to indicate that a field is the owner of relationship to a list of entities that extend Model.
    HasOne
    This annotation is used to indicate that a field is the owner of relationship to an entity that extends Model.
    Index
    Index annotates any Model with the index that will be configured in the persistence layer.
    Indexes
    Indexes allows an instance of Model to be annotated with multiple Index.
    Indices
    Indices allows an instance of Model to be annotated with multiple Index.
    ModelConfig
    ModelConfig annotates any Model with applicable configuration information.
    ModelField
    This annotation is used to indicate that a member of a class which extends Model should be serialized or deserialized into the DataStore.
